modules.description: Processes a file as a template, injecting content and variables using a specified data injectable module. Operates on path structures and returns task-based results with parsed data and strings. Used to dynamically generate content from template files with variable substitution.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates on configuration files and project directories. Used to set up a local build context and compile project artifacts efficiently.

Generates dynamic content by processing template files with variable substitution using path structures and task-based results. Supports data injection through a dedicated module, enabling flexible content customization. Parses templates into executable forms, allowing for runtime rendering with structured data. Examples include generating HTML pages with user-specific data or creating configuration files with dynamic values.
